sample information csv row index numbers for the table
sample information csv sample id area sample identification number re used annually e g sitka 1 (sitka sound) and sitka 2 (hoonah sound) denote the two samples collected in the sitka area annually
sample information csv slide unique slide number associated with an area sample id for the purpose of collecting scales for age determination 20 scales were fixed to each of four slides
sample information csv fish in combination with the area sample id and slide the fish identifies the specific fish sampled on that date (e g sitka 1 slide 1 fish 1)
sample information csv sex sex of the fish sampled (male or female)
sample information csv stdlen standard length is the strait line distance from the tip of the upper jaw to the posterior end of the hypural plate (anderson and gutreuter 1983)

sample information csv forklen fork length is the strait line distance from the most anterior part of the fish to the terminus of the median caudal fin rays (anderson and gutreuter 1983) it may include the projecting lower jaw
sample information csv weight whole body weight in grams
sample information csv wtdsc description of the weight (whole body weight in grams)
column5: of molluscs ash free dry weight

column3: sample information csv age age of the herring sampled as estimated by counting putative annuli on a scale removed from the left side of the fish two rows below the lateral line in line above the center of the pectoral fin
sample information csv comments misc comments recorded by the sample collector scale reader etc
sample information csv sin unique sample identification number
sample information csv maturity gonad maturity (e g immature green ripe spent)
sample information csv latitude approximate latitude at the location the sample was collected (decimal degrees wgs 84)
sample information csv longitude approximate longitude at the location the sample was collected (decimal degrees wgs 84)
sample information csv species latin name (genus species) of the fish sampled (e g clupea pallasii)
sample information csv collector name name of the person responsible for collecting that particular sample
sample information csv tissue1 type of tissue collected (e g heart for fatty acid analysis)
sample information csv tissue2 type of tissue collected (e g otolith for elemental analysis)
sample information csv tissue3 type of tissue collected (e g caudal fin for genetic analysis)
column5: whale photo right dorsal fin identifier

column3: sample information csv heart the number 1 signifies that the heart from that particular fish (sin) was randomly selected for processing to determine fatty acid composition a blank cell denotes the heart was not processed

sample information csv otocore the number 1 signifies that the otolith core from that particular fish (sin) was randomly selected for processing to determine the micro chemistry of the otolith core a blank cell denotes the otolith core was not processed
sample information csv project evos project id number (e g 070769)

sample information csv otoedge the number 1 signifies that the otolith edge from that particular fish (sin) was randomly selected for processing to determine the micro chemistry of the otolith edge a blank cell denotes the otolith edge was not processed
sample information csv fin no fish were processed for genetic analysis in this study so all cells are blank all caudal fins collected in this study were archived for future genetic analysis
column5: time in depth bin above sfc proportion

column3: sample information csv no heart denotes fish that were sampled for otolith chemistry but not heart fatty acids
